# Banking System API Testing

## ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Role-Based Access Control
# Each endpoint requires a specific role:
# - /admin/** → Requires ADMIN role (login as "admin")
# - /teller/** → Requires TELLER role (login as "teller1") 
# - /client/** → Requires CLIENT role (login as "client1")
# - /auth/** → No authentication required

## Step 1: Test Login First
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Expected Response:
# {
#   "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9...",
#   "role": "ADMIN"
# }
# Copy the token value (without quotes) for the next requests

## Step 2: Test Admin Endpoints (Replace YOUR_TOKEN_HERE with actual token)

### ✅ List All Tellers (FIRST - get the IDs!)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admin/tellers
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### ✅ Create New Teller
POST http://localhost:8080/api/admin/tellers
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testteller",
  "password": "password123"
}

### ✅ Update Teller Password (use real ID from list above, e.g., 1, 2, 3...)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/admin/tellers/1/password
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testteller",
  "password": "newpassword123"
}

### ✅ Delete Teller (use real ID from list above, e.g., 1, 2, 3...)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/admin/tellers/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

## Error Testing - Wrong Role Access

### ❌ Try Admin Token on Teller Endpoint (should return 403 Forbidden)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/teller/clients
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

### ❌ Try Client Token on Admin Endpoint (should return 403 Forbidden)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admin/tellers
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLIENT_TOKEN_HERE

### ❌ Try Teller Token on Client Endpoint (should return 403 Forbidden)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/client/accounts
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TELLER_TOKEN_HERE

## Step 3: Test Teller Endpoints (Login as teller1 first)

### Login as Teller
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "teller1",
  "password": "123456"
}

### List All Clients
GET http://localhost:8080/api/teller/clients
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TELLER_TOKEN_HERE

### Create New Client
POST http://localhost:8080/api/teller/clients
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TELLER_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testclient",
  "password": "password123"
}

## Step 4: Test Client Endpoints (Login as client1 first)

### Login as Client
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "client1",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Get My Accounts
GET http://localhost:8080/api/client/accounts
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLIENT_TOKEN_HERE

### Request New Account
POST http://localhost:8080/api/client/accounts/request
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLIENT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currency": "USD"
}

## Error Testing

### Test Without Token (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admin/tellers

### Test With Invalid Token (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admin/tellers
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### Test Wrong Role (use client token on admin endpoint - should return 403)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admin/tellers
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLIENT_TOKEN_HERE